# chord `pitch`: sets the minimum pitch of the lowest chord note. The lowest
# note placed is the chord note nearest AT OR ABOVE pitch. C major 7 (default),
# pitch = 0.0166667 (semi 2 = D). The chord note nearest above D is E (semi 4),
# so E becomes the lowest and the voicing rises from there within one octave.
#   voice pcs C/E/G/B anchored on E(4): C->12, E->4, G->7, B->11
#   O1=C(semi 12), O2=E(4), O3=G(7), O4=B(11)
patch <<<
[chord]
    pitch   = 0.0166667
    output1 = O1
    output2 = O2
    output3 = O3
    output4 = O4
>>>
@0 expect O1 0.1 tol 1e-5
@0 expect O2 0.0333333 tol 1e-5
@0 expect O3 0.0583333 tol 1e-5
@0 expect O4 0.0916667 tol 1e-5
